52
00:03:08,786 --> 00:03:11,786
Abelheim, please come to me, my child.

53
00:03:14,033 --> 00:03:18,033
Is the grandmother already here, Mrs. Rottenmeier?

54
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:22,033
Adelheid, how many times do I have to tell you to knock?

55
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:23,033
That was on purpose.

56
00:03:23,033 --> 00:03:26,033
I don't want to be on purpose. Go out right now!

57
00:03:26,033 --> 00:03:27,033
Yes.

58
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:28,033
We'll practice until you can do it.

59
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:32,033
Imagine I'm Mrs. Sesemann and you come in to greet me.

60
00:03:38,033 --> 00:03:39,033
Hi!

61
00:03:39,473 --> 00:03:40,973
Hello, Mrs. Rottenmeier.

62
00:03:40,973 --> 00:03:42,973
Of course.

63
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:45,973
It's not called Mrs. Rottenmeier and not at all hello!

64
00:03:45,973 --> 00:03:47,973
I am Mrs. Sesemann, understood?

65
00:03:47,973 --> 00:03:49,973
I see.

66
00:03:49,973 --> 00:03:52,973
You come in and ask, how are you, Mrs. Sesemann?

67
00:03:52,973 --> 00:03:53,973
Where is Mrs. Sesemann?

68
00:03:53,973 --> 00:03:56,473
It has no purpose, it has no purpose.

69
00:03:56,473 --> 00:03:57,973
You should speak loudly.

70
00:03:57,973 --> 00:03:58,973
Where is she?

71
00:03:58,973 --> 00:03:59,973
Calm down!

72
00:03:59,973 --> 00:04:01,473
No one can be so stupid.

73
00:04:01,473 --> 00:04:02,973
We start from the beginning.

74
00:04:04,473 --> 00:04:06,973
Good day, grandmother, how are you?

75
00:04:07,143 --> 00:04:10,143
Who gave you permission to call her grandmother?

76
00:04:10,143 --> 00:04:12,643
No one, but I'm sure she will.

77
00:04:12,643 --> 00:04:16,643
She is the grandmother of Mrs. Clara and only she has the permission to call her
that.

78
00:04:16,643 --> 00:04:18,643
All the others call her kind lady.

79
00:04:18,643 --> 00:04:19,643
Why?

80
00:04:19,643 --> 00:04:23,143
Remember well, Mrs. Sesemann is the lady of this house.

81
00:04:23,143 --> 00:04:25,643
We have to meet her with great pride.

82
00:04:25,643 --> 00:04:30,643
She is a fine old lady and she knows exactly how to appreciate good behavior, my
child.

83
00:04:30,643 --> 00:04:34,143
She does not deserve any noise and no impudence near her.

84
00:04:34,263 --> 00:04:37,663
And if you move aside, it will fall back on me.

85
00:04:37,663 --> 00:04:40,263
But Clara said she is very nice.

86
00:04:40,263 --> 00:04:41,663
Of course she is.

87
00:04:41,663 --> 00:04:44,263
Besides, she demands absolute obedience.

88
00:04:44,263 --> 00:04:47,263
Then she's not a grandmother, then she's like you.

89
00:04:47,263 --> 00:04:49,263
Nobility, you're talking nonsense.

90
00:04:49,263 --> 00:04:51,263
I'm not talking nonsense.

91
00:04:51,263 --> 00:04:54,663
That's part of it, too. The kind lady doesn't want any objection.

92
00:04:54,663 --> 00:04:55,663
Good.

93
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:59,463
What's going on again?

94
00:04:59,463 --> 00:05:01,463
What's wrong with the picture, Sebastian?

95
00:05:01,655 --> 00:05:03,855
I wanted to hang it on the wall. That's all.

96
00:05:03,855 --> 00:05:05,855
Why? There's already a picture hanging on the wall.

97
00:05:05,855 --> 00:05:09,155
I wanted to exchange it. This is the favorite picture of the Blessed Virgin.

98
00:05:09,155 --> 00:05:10,955
That's pure waste of time.

99
00:05:10,955 --> 00:05:12,555
But I thought...

100
00:05:12,555 --> 00:05:14,855
They shouldn't think, they should do their job.

101
00:05:14,855 --> 00:05:16,755
And what they do, that's what I decide.

102
00:05:16,755 --> 00:05:17,855
Yes, ma'am.

103
00:05:19,755 --> 00:05:21,355
Wait a moment!

104
00:05:21,355 --> 00:05:23,755
What are you wearing over your arm, Tinette?

105
00:05:23,755 --> 00:05:24,755
Fork angel.

106
00:05:24,755 --> 00:05:27,655
Are you both making fun of me or what's going on here?

107
00:05:27,655 --> 00:05:30,055
What do you want to start with these curtains?

108
00:05:30,055 --> 00:05:30,955
Hang them up.

109
00:05:30,983 --> 00:05:33,683
The noble lady prefers bright colors in the house.

110
00:05:33,683 --> 00:05:37,183
Mr. Sesemann has transferred me the management of his household.

111
00:05:37,183 --> 00:05:41,183
And I can't remember that I gave the order to exchange the curtains.

112
00:05:43,283 --> 00:05:46,983
Oh, there she is! What are you standing around for? Hurry up!

113
00:05:48,683 --> 00:05:52,383
And you, Adelheid, please don't forget what we practiced together earlier.

114
00:05:52,383 --> 00:05:55,383
You make a knick and ask, how are you, noble lady?

115
00:05:55,383 --> 00:05:57,183
Say yes, not grandmother to her!

116
00:05:57,183 --> 00:05:58,783
Oh dear, she's coming.

117
